{{Organization Page}} =Description= [[File:sfi_logo.jpg|thumb]] At the [https://www.forests.org/ Sustainable Forestry Initiative¬Æ Inc.], we believe that sustainable forests are critical to our collective future. SFI¬Æ is a sustainability leader through our work in standards, conservation, community, and education. As an independent, non-profit organization, we collaborate with our diverse network to provide solutions to local and global sustainability challenges. SFI works with the forest sector, brand owners, conservation groups, resource professionals, landowners, educators, local communities, Indigenous Peoples, governments, and universities.
[https://sfidatabase.org/ Database of SFI Certified Forests] ==Mission== is to advance sustainability through forest-focused collaborations. ==Vision== is a world that values and benefits from sustainably managed forests. ==Culture== SFI believes in creating an empowered and supportive team that is committed to enhancing the value of forests for our shared equality of life now and in the future. Read more about SFI culture.
