{{Organization Page}} =Description= [http://www.kwconservation.org/ KIWA Conservation Team] is a collaborative network of public and private partners working to ensure the long‚Äêterm sustainability of the Kirtland‚Äôs Warbler. The KWCT is made up of a steering committee, several sub-committees established to address specific issues, and others interested in the conservation of Kirtland‚Äôs Warblers.
==What do we do?== The Mission of the Kirtland‚Äôs Warbler Conservation Team is to steward the communication and cooperation among federal, state, non-governmental organizations, universities, and other partners to ensure the long-term sustainability of the Kirtland‚Äôs Warbler and its breeding, wintering and migratory habitats (associated habitats).
