=Description= Most abundant wintering populations in the Bahamas. Found that goat farming creates good wintering habitat for [[Kirtland's Warbler]]s. * Keep vegetation short, early succession (ideal habitat types) * Goats require water (needed for warblers) * Goats fenced (doesn't impact surrounding habitat) * Generates income, cost-effective (demand for meat exceeds Bahama's production)
